@emmett9001 this is only an issue if you 1) call `produce()` and then 2) immediately get to the end of the program, so that the interpreter starts cleaning up.

In that case, `Producer.__del__()` may run before the queues are empty, and that will call `stop()`, which will wait for `queue_reader` to flush, but this will fail: at the point where `__del__` runs the weakref is no longer dereferenceable.

Getting rid of the weakref would require quite a reshuffle of `Producer` I'm afraid: the problem is that `queue_reader` calls `_send_request()`. I think it would not be illogical if that were a method of `OwnedBroker` instead, but it is a bit of a job to separate it from `Producer`.

